  "prompt": "What is the best way to clean a flat screen monitor?",
  "response": "Here are the best practices for cleaning a flat screen monitor:\n\n1. Materials needed:\n- Soft, lint-free microfiber cloth\n- Distilled water\n- Isopropyl alcohol (optional)\n\n2. Steps:\n- Turn off and unplug the monitor\n- Use a dry microfiber cloth to gently remove dust\n- For stubborn smudges, slightly dampen the cloth with distilled water\n- Gently wipe the screen in a circular motion\n- Do not apply excessive pressure\n- Let the screen air dry\n\n3. Things to avoid:\n- Paper towels or rough cloths\n- Regular tap water\n- Glass cleaners\n- Cleaning solutions with alcohol or ammonia\n- Spraying liquid directly on the screen\n- Pressing hard on the screen\n\n4. Additional tips:\n- Clean your monitor periodically\n- Use a screen-specific cleaning solution if desired\n- Follow manufacturer's specific cleaning recommendations\n\n5. Frequency:\n- Dust weekly\n- Deep clean monthly or as needed\n\nAlways be gentle and use the least aggressive cleaning method first to protect your screen's delicate surface.",
